oices From Heaven|The Last Voices From Heaven Parts 1 & 2]]'' ([[Foxtel]])\n**''Moulin Rouge Girls'' ([[ABC1|ABC TV]])\n**''Stories From a Children's Hospital: Chloe's Story'' (ABC TV)\n**''Tug of Love'' (SBS TV)\n|}\n\n==Performers==\n*[[Mario (American singer)|Mario]]<ref name=\"Logies History\"/>\n*The cast of ''[[Neighbours]]''<ref name=\"Logies History\"/>\n*The cast of ''Grease: The Arena Spectacular''<ref name=\"Logies History\"/>\n*[[Il Divo]]<ref name=\"Logies History\"/>\n*[[Michael Bubl\u00e9]]<ref name=\"Logies History\"/>\n\n==Hall of Fame==\nAfter 20 years on Australian television, ''[[Neighbours]]'' became the 22nd inductee into the TV Week Logies [[List of Logie Hall of Fame|Hall of Fame]].<ref name=\"winners\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb event|0000401/2005}}\n\n{{Logie Awards years}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Logie Awards Of 2005}}\n[[Category:Logie Awards|2005]]\n[[Category:2005 television awards]]\n[[Category:2005 in Australian television]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Australian English|date=April 2014}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| award            = Logie Awards\n| number           = 47\n| image            =\n| image_size       = \n| caption          = \n| date             = 1 May 2005\n| site             = [[Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex#The Palladium Room|Crown Palladium]], [[Melbourne]], Victoria\n| host             = [[Eddie McGuire]]<br>[[Andrew O'Keefe]]<br>[[Rove McManus]]\n| gold             = [[Rove McManus]]\n| hall_of_fame     = ''[[Neighbours]]''\n| most_wins        = ''[[Rove (TV series)|Rove (Live)]]'' (3)\n| most_nominations = ''[[Home and Away]]'' (8)\n| network          = [[Nine Network]]\n| last             = [[Logie Awards of 2004|46th]]\n| next             = [[Logie Awards of 2006|48th]]\n}}\nThe '''47th Annual [[TV Week]] [[Logie Award]]s''' was held on Sunday 1 May 2005 at the [[Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex#The Palladium Room|Crown Palladium]] in [[Melbourne]], and broadcast on the [[Nine Network]].<ref name=\"Logies History\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tvweeklogieawards.com.au/logie-history/2000s/2005/ |title=47th TV Week Logie Awards, 2005 |publisher=Tvweeklogies.com.au |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140126184012/http://www.tvweeklogieawards.com.au/logie-history/2000s/2005/ |archivedate=26 January 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In an historic first, the ceremony was hosted by [[Eddie McGuire]], [[Andrew O'Keefe]] and [[Rove McManus]].<ref name=\"Logies History\"/> Special guests included [[Kathryn Morris]] and [[Adam Rodr\u00edguez]].<ref name=\"Logies History\"/>\n\n==Winners and nominees==\nIn the tables below, winners are listed first and highlighted in '''bold'''.<ref name=\"winners\">{{cite web|url=http://www.australiantelevision.net/awards/logie2005.html|title=2005 Logie Awards|publisher=Australiantelevision.net|accessdate=20 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"smhlogie\">{{cite news |last1=Idato |first1=Michael |title=Once, twice, three times a Gold Logie |work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |url=https://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/once-twice-three-times-a-gold-logie-20050502-gdl8io.html |department=News and Features | page=3|date=2 May 2005}}</ref>\n\n===Gold Logie===\n{| class=wikitable width=\"50%\"\n|-\n! width=\"25%\"| [[Gold Logie Award for Most Popular Personality on Australian Television|Most Popular Personality on Australian Television]]\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n*'''[[Rove McManus]] in ''[[Rove (TV series)|Rove (Live)]]'' ([[Network Ten]])'''\n**[[Bridie Carter]] in ''[[McLeod's Daughters]]'' ([[Nine Network]])\n**[[Bec Cartwright]] in ''[[Home and Away]]'' ([[Seven Network]])\n**[[Georgie Parker]] in ''[[All Saints (TV series)|All Saints]]'' (Seven Network)\n**[[John Wood (Australian actor)|John Wood]] in ''[[Blue Heelers]]'' (Seven Network)\n|}\n\n===Acting/Presenting===\n{| class=wikitable width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! width=\"25%\"| [[Logie Award for Most Popular Act